## SDD / TDD / harness

- **Specs:** Number product specs `S-001`, `S-002`, … (`project/specs/S-XXX-<slug>.md`). Reference the active spec id in plans and PRs when changing behaviour.
- **ADRs:** Number architecture decisions `ADR-0001`, `ADR-0002`, … New ADRs in `project/docs/adr/` using `project/docs/adr/_template.md`. Reference ADRs in prose as `ADR-NNNN`.
- **Traceability:** Tasks should cite which acceptance criteria (`AC-N`) they satisfy; commits may use `Closes: S-XXX#AC-N`.
- **Glossary:** New domain nouns belong in `project/docs/domain-glossary.md` (or reuse existing terms). Do not invent parallel vocabulary.
- **Harness:** Prefer typed boundaries, glossary alignment, and shared test harness factories/doubles under `<TEST_HARNESS_ROOT>` so agents and humans share the same seams — see `project/docs/test-harness.md`.

